As outlined above, allocating species to genera among the emeralds has been fraught with difficulties. While we would like to preserve diagnosability of genera and retain what is salvageable of existing nomenclature in the interests of stability, our goal has been to bring the results into as close a concordance as possible with the branching pattern and branch lengths in the genetic tree (
McGuire et al . 2014
). Where no clear recommendation was possible, we have clearly presented the options. To help clarify the latter, we present a list of the generic names mentioned above, when and in what form they were proposed, their type species, and when and by whom these had been fixed in Appendix 1, and we summarize our recommendations as a revised list of genera and species of the Trochilini in Appendix 2.
